        <page n="02" image="va.au.ss.1857.07.15.02">
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>What Will They Do?</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Editorial about Kansas. Notes the different Southern conventions making
                    recommendations, blames the Democrats for stirring up trouble.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Blue Ridge Tunnel</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>Predictions notwithstanding, the tunnel will not be completed for another 6
                    months. SS thinks that the progress is a bit too slow.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Concert</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Under the tuition of Mr. Turner, the members of the band have made
                    astonishing progress and will ere long be proficients in their department of
                    music.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Turner</ln>
                        <pf>A. J.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Sax Horn Band will be performing at Union Hall; SS highly recommends
                it.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Mr. Davis' Nursery</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Davis</ln>
                        <pf>Franklin</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Endorsement of Davis' local nursery. He has thousands of fruit trees, and
                    many beautiful flowers to interest the ladies.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>Harvest</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names/>
                <summary>More about the wheat harvest. Even though it is unprecedentedly late, it
                    appears to be quite good.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>2</column>
                <head>More of a good thing</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Young</ln>
                        <fn>W. B.</fn>
                        <pf>Dr.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>SS suggests that people visit the new soda fountain in Young's drug store,
                    to refresh themselves in the summer heat.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>1</column>
                <head>Washington College</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt/>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer/>
                <names>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Massie</ln>
                        <pf>J. L.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>Christian</ln>
                        <pf>M. H.</pf>
                    </name>
                    <name>
                        <ln>McCue</ln>
                        <pf>John H.</pf>
                    </name>
                </names>
                <summary>Report on commencement at Washington college. Bottom is too blurry to
                read.</summary>
            </div>
            <div type="a">
                <column>3</column>
                <head>Our New Market</head>
                <origin/>
                <commentary/>
                <excerpt>Let the young ladies and gentlemen, instead of snoozing lazily in their
                    beds, rise with the sun, and hie to the market, and we can soon make it not only
                    a useful institution but a charming place of resort.</excerpt>
                <transcript/>
                <trailer>Some of the Aggreived</trailer>
                <names/>
                <summary>SS wondering when the new market house will be completed; not having one is
                    very injurous to the town. Its residents are inconvenienced and it prevents
                    newcomers from settling.</summary>
            </div>
            <pageNote>Report on the Henry Clay Monument and the restoration of Mt.
            Vernon.</pageNote>
        </page>
